South Africa’s confirmed coronavirus cases have jumped to 657 627 with 2 055 new cases  identified in the last 24 hours. The Health Department has also reported a further 85 COVID-19 related deaths, bringing the death toll to 15 857. The number of recoveries is at 586 844 translating to a 89.2% recovery rate.    #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 18 September. Use the COVID Alert SA app to protect yourself, your loved ones and your community. Start using this privacy preserving app today. Add your phone to the fight! Download the Covid Alert SA app now! https://t.co/8YKEqaiiRF pic.twitter.com/IY2CfxSNWq — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) September 18, 2020  Below is the health department’s statement on the latest information:  